# Frontend Conventions

Full design system: `docs/ui.md`. Match `frontend/src/pages/Users.tsx` as the reference page.

## Styling

- Import `T`, `pick`, and menu helpers from `frontend/src/theme/designTokens.ts`. Do not fork token objects or hardcode core-color hex values.
- Data views use the flex-list primitives in `frontend/src/components/ui/` (`ListShell`, `ColumnHeader`, `ListDataRow`, `DialogListPagination`). Filters use the toggled inline strip + `FilterToken` (no drawer).

## Interaction (never use browser-native modals)

```tsx
// ❌ BAD
if (window.confirm('Delete?')) { ... }
alert('Failed');

// ✅ GOOD
const confirm = useConfirm();      // frontend/src/hooks/useConfirm.tsx
const { showError, showSuccess } = useSnackbar();  // frontend/src/hooks/useSnackbar.tsx
if (await confirm({ title: 'Delete permission?', ... })) { ... }
```

- Date/time inputs: use `components/DateTimePicker.tsx`, never native `datetime-local`.
- Autofocus the first meaningful input in dialogs.

## Data, errors, permissions

- Surface API errors with `getApiErrorMessage(e)` (`frontend/src/utils/apiError.ts`) — it includes backend hints.
- Track a `loadError` state per fetch and render an MUI `Alert` for failures, distinct from empty states.
- Gate destructive UI with `usePermissions()` (`hasPermission(...)`, and `canTakeAction` when only super admins may act). This is UX only — the backend still enforces.
